  <steps>
    <step num="0">Preheat oven to 450°F (230°C). </step>
    <step num="1">Slice the baguette into ½-inch (1 cm) rounds and place on a baking sheet. </step>
    <step num="2">Brush both sides of the baguette slices with olive oil. </step>
    <step num="3">Bake for for 6 minutes until slightly crispy. </step>
    <step num="4">In a medium bowl, combine the tomatoes, minced garlic, balsamic vinegar, basil, salt, and pepper. </step>
    <step num="5">Rub the garlic into one side of the baguette slices, then spoon the tomato mixture evenly across the slices. </step>
    <step num="6">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
